  "response": "Apple changed its name from Apple Computers Incorporated to Apple Inc. on January 9, 2007. This decision was made to reflect the company's expanding focus beyond just computers. By that time, Apple had already successfully launched products like the iPod and was on the cusp of introducing the iPhone. The new name was more inclusive of their broader range of consumer electronics, software, and services.",
